  "title": "Le présent des verbes en -ir (finir, choisir…)",
  "type": "fill",
  "lesson": "Regular -ir verbs follow this pattern in the present tense: je finis, tu finis, il/elle finit, nous finissons, vous finissez, ils/elles finissent. Note the -iss- infix in the plural forms (nous, vous, ils/elles), which distinguishes these verbs from other -ir verbs.",
